730265f-b.title: General view - [Manhattan - 39th Street (West) - 6th Avenue.]
730265f-b.text:
65 W. 39th Street, at the N. E. corner of Sixth Avenue,
(general View westward).
A set of two views towards and aoross Broadway at 39th Street,
showing there an excavation for the 33 story Bricken-Casino Building
(No. 1410 Broadway) and low structures opposite. Beyond the latter
appear structures on Seventh Avernue, the three in the center being,
the 43 story Navarre Building (No. 508 Seventh Avenue), the 22 story
Fashion Center Building (rear view, No. 521'Seventh Avenue), and the
300 story structure, No. 528 Seventh Avenue. To the right foreground
and with tower atop, is the 23 story, Lefcourt Manhattan Building
(No. 1412 Broadway).
